long the way, with the help of such diverse thinkers as Saussure, Barthes, Foucault, Derrida, and Bloom, Lentricchia indicates a strategy by which future critical theorists may resist the mandarin attitudes of their fathers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aCriticismxHistoryy20th century. 0aCriticismzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  acontemporary, modern, america, american, theory, theoretical, critical, critique, academic, scholarly, research, european, context, contextual, culture, cultural, philosophy, philosophical, analysis, frye, stevens, kermode, sartre, poulet, heidegger, sussure, barthes, levi strauss, derrida, foucault, krieger, hirsch, de man, bloom, formalist, new, history, historical, society, thinkers, social.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package Archive 1960-1989z978311066784440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226229058423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226229058/original  a978-3-11-066784-4  University of Chicago Press eBook Package Archive 1960-1989c1960d1989  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles